Times|date=September 18, 2013}}</ref> Before the rescheduling from 2014 to 2015, a ''[[Monsters University]]'' short film titled ''[[Party Central]]'' was set to accompany the film, but was instead shown with the theatrical release of Disney's ''[[Muppets Most Wanted]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Fischer|first=Russ|title=\u2018Monsters University\u2019 Short Film \u2018Party Central\u2019 Revealed|url=http://www.slashfilm.com/disney-debuts-monsters-u-short-party-central-at-d23/|accessdate=August 9, 2013|newspaper=/Film|date=August 9, 2013}}</ref> In April 2015, it was announced that a new Pixar short, ''[[Sanjay's Super Team]]'', directed by Sanjay Patel, would be shown in front of ''The Good Dinosaur'' instead.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Keegan|first1=Rebecca|title=Pixar artist Sanjay Patel gets personal with 'Sanjay's Super Team'|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-pixar-short-sanjay-super-team-20150429-story.html|accessdate=April 28, 2015|work=Los Angeles Times|date=April 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe film's [[Trailer (promotion)|teaser trailer]] was released on June 2, 2015,<ref>Eliana Dockterman, [http://time.com/3905762/the-good-dinosaur-trailer-pixar/ \"Go Back in Time With the First Trailer for Pixar's The Good Dinosaur,\"] ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', June 2, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/trailers/446043-the-teaser-trailer-and-poster-for-pixars-the-good-dinosaur#/slide/1 \"The Teaser Trailer and Poster for Pixar's The Good Dinosaur,\"] [[ComingSoon.net]], June 2, 2015.</ref> and the first official trailer was released on July 21, 2015.<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O-RgquKVTPE|title=The Good Dinosaur - Official US Trailer|date=July 21, 2015|work=YouTube|accessdate=July 25, 2015}}</ref> The film received an exclusive run at the [[Grand Rex]] in [[Paris]] a week before its U.S. and European premiere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/paris-attacks-spectre-prevails-france-840427|title=Paris Attacks: 'Spectre' Prevails in France Despite Cinema Closures|first=Pamela|last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=November 15, 2015|accessdate=November 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n''The Good Dinosaur'' was released by [[Walt Disney Studios Home Entertainment]] on [[Blu-ray]] (2D and 3D), [[DVD-Video|DVD]], and [[Digital distribution|digital download]] in the United States on February 23, 2016. Blu-ray bonus features include ''Sanjay's Super Team'', audio commentary, behind-the-scenes featurettes, deleted scenes, and the \"Hide and Seek\" short promotional clip.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Szadkowski|first1=Joseph|title=Blu-ray review: The Good Dinosaur, Pixar\u2019s prehistoric travelogue|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2016/feb/25/blu-ray-review-good-dinosaur-pixars-prehistoric/|accessdate=February 26, 2016|work=The Washington Times|date=February 25, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u2018The Good Dinosaur\u2019 on 3D Blu-ray on February with Deleted Scenes, Original Short (Sneak Peek)|url=http://www.stitchkingdom.com/disney-the-good-dinoaur-on-3d-blu-ray-on-february-with-original-short-sneak-peek-83547/|publisher=Stitch Kingdom|accessdate=March 10, 2016|date=January 22, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125224941/http://www.stitchkingdom.com/disney-the-good-dinoaur-on-3d-blu-ray-on-february-with-original-short-sneak-peek-83547/#|archive-date=January 25, 2016|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> ''The Good Dinosaur'' was released on [[Ultra HD Blu-ray|4K UHD Blu-ray]] on September 10, 2019.<ref>{{Citation|title=The Good Dinosaur 4K Blu-ray|url=https://www.blu-ray.com/movies/The-Good-Dinosaur-4K-Blu-ray/246045/|access-date=2019-08-02}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''The Good Dinosaur'' grossed $123.1 million in the United States and Canada and $209.1 million in other countries, for a worldwide total of $332.2 million<ref name=\"BOM\"/> against a production budget of $175\u2013200 million,<ref name=\"McLintock (2015-11-23)\">{{cite news |first=Pamela |last=McClintock |title=Box-Office Thanksgiving Preview: 'Good Dinosaur' Takes On 'Hunger Games: Mockingjay' |date=November 23, 2015 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-thanksgiving-preview-good-843104 |accessdate=December 10, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Faughnder (2015-11-24)\">{{Cite news |last=Faughnder |first=Ryan |title='Good Dinosaur' and 'Creed' to battle 'Hunger Games' at holiday box office |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=November 24, 2015 |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-et-ct-creed-good-dinosaur-hunger-games-20151124-story.html |accessdate=December 10, 2015}}</ref> Adding in the marketing budget, the film had a cost of $350 million,<ref>{{cite web|last1=McClintock|first1=Pamela|title='Good Dinosaur': Analyzing Pixar's First Box-Office Disaster|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/good-dinosaur-analyzing-pixars-first-857317|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016}}</ref> which it was [[List of biggest box-office bombs|unable to recoup]]\u2014causing [[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Walt Disney Studios]] to lose $85 million unadjusted for inflation.<ref name=\"Guerrasio\">{{cite web|last1=Guerrasio|first1=Jason|title='Pixar finally has its first box-office bomb|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/pixar-finally-has-its-first-box-office-bomb-2015-12|website=[[Business Insider]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016}}</ref><ref>Brew, Simon, [http://www.denofgeek.us/movies/the-good-dinosaur/252357/the-good-dinosaur-is-pixars-lowest-grossing-movie \"The Good Dinosaur is Pixar's Lowest Grossing Movie\"], Den of Geek!, January 7, 2016, Retrieved April 7, 2016.</ref><ref>[http://www.boxofficemojo.com/franchises/chart/?id=pixar.htm \"Pixar Total Grosses\"], Box Office Mojo, Retrieved April 7, 2016.</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kenny|first1=Charles|title='Pixar\u2019s First Flop is Being Quietly Swept Under the Rug|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2016/01/pixars-first-flop-is-being-quietly-swept-under-the-rug-122418/|website=[[IndieWire]]|accessdate=November 13, 2016}}</ref> However, the film proved to be much more financially successful in home video sales.<ref>{{cite web|last1=McKnight|first1=Brent|title=The Good Dinosaur Somehow Managed To Find Its Audience On Home Video|url=http://www.cinemablend.com/new/Good-Dinosaur-Somehow-Managed-Find-Its-Audience-Home-Video-116267.html|website=Cinema Blend|accessdate=July 9, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Arnold|first1=Thomas K.|title=Pixar\u2019s \u2018Good Dinosaur\u2019 Tops Home Video Sales Charts|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/pixars-good-dinosaur-tops-home-video-sales-charts-1201721351/|website=Variety.com|accessdate=July 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn North America, ''The Good Dinosaur'' opened on Wednesday, November 25, 2015 alongside ''[[Creed (film)|Creed]]'' and ''[[Victor Frankenstein (film)|Victor Frankenstein]]'', as well as the wide releases of ''[[Brooklyn (film)|Brooklyn]]'', ''[[Spotlight (film)|Spotlight]]'', and ''[[Trumbo (2015 film)|Trumbo]]''. The film was projected to gross $60\u201365 million from 3,749 theaters in its first five days, including $45 million in its opening weekend.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/thanksgiving-day-box-office-hunger-games-mockingjay-dinosaur-creed-1201635844/ |title= Katniss To Sling Arrows Into \u2018Creed\u2019 & \u2018Victor Frankenstein\u2019, As \u2018Good Dinosaur\u2019 Stalks Families: Thanksgiving B.O. Preview |website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref> It made $1.3 million from its Tuesday night previews and $9.8 million on its first day. The film ended up grossing $55.6 million in its first five days, including $39.2 million in its opening weekend, finishing second at the box office behind the second weekend of ''[[The Hunger Games: Mockingjay \u2013 Part 2]]''.<ref name=\"CinemaScore\"/>\n\nOutside North America, it earned $28.7 million from 39 markets, including 8 significant markets. Unlike the US, where it had the benefit of the Thanksgiving weekend, it did not have the same benefit internationally. Rather, its release date was designed to set it up to run through the December holiday.<ref name=\"Overseas17thOpening\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/hunger-games-mockingjay-part-2-good-dinosaur-martian-china-international-box-office-results-1201645755/|title=\u2018Mockingjay\u2019 Rules Roost; \u2018Good Dinosaur\u2019 Hatches With $29M; \u2018The Martian\u2019 Lands $50M In China \u2013 Intl Box Office|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=November 29, 2015|accessdate=November 30, 2015}}</ref> The top openings were in the United Kingdom ($4.3 million), Mexico ($3.6 million), France ($3.2 million), Argentina ($2.2 million), and Russia ($2.1 million). Of those, it opened at No. 1 in Mexico, Argentina and Russia.<ref name=\"Overseas19thOpening\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/12/mockingjay-part-2-spectre-the-martian-point-break-good-dinosaur-heart-sea-krampus-international-box-office-results-1201655479/|title=\u2018In The Heart Of The Sea\u2019, \u2018Point Break\u2019 Surf Into Top 5 With Offshore Debuts \u2013 International Box Office Update|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=December 6, 2015|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref> In terms of total earnings, its leading markets are the United Kingdom ($10.1 million), Mexico ($8.7 million), and France ($8.1 million).<ref name=\"Overseas20thOpening\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/12/mockingjay-part-2-good-dinosaur-spectre-heart-of-the-sea-point-break-star-wars-international-box-office-results-1201666009/|title=China Makes \u2018Surprise\u2019 Entrance At No. 1; Katniss, Arlo & 007 Top Calm Studio Frame \u2013 Intl Box Office Update|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=December 13, 2015|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nThe [[review aggregation]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] gives the film a rating of 76%, based on 214 reviews, with a rating average of 6.59/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"''The Good Dinosaur'' delivers thrillingly beautiful animation in service of a worthy story that, even if it doesn't quite live up to the lofty standards set by Pixar, still adds up to charming, family-friendly entertainment.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_good_dinosaur/ |title=''The Good Dinosaur'' (2015) |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a [[Weighted arithmetic mean|weighted average]] score of 66 out of 100, based on reviews from 37 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews.\"<ref name=\"metacritic\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-good-dinosaur |title=''The Good Dinosaur'' Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=November 28, 2015}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale.<ref name=\"CinemaScore\">{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/thanksgiving-box-office-hunger-games-mockingjay-creed-the-good-dinosaur-1201639941/ |title=Katniss Rules Wednesday On Track For $78M-80M 5-Day; \u2018Good Dinosaur\u2019 Eyes $58M-$62M; \u2018Creed\u2019 Punching $39M-$42M |author=Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=November 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nKenneth Turan of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' described it as \"antic and unexpected as well as homiletic, rife with subversive elements, wacky critters and some of the most beautiful landscapes ever seen in a computer animated film.\"<ref name=\"lat\">{{cite news|title=Review: 'The Good Dinosaur' is a wondrous, wacky Jurassic world for tykes|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|first=Kenneth|last=Turan|date=November 25, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-good-dinosaur-review-20151125-column.html}}</ref> Manohla Dargis of ''[[The New York Times]]'' felt the film \"has a few things on its mind, but its tone is overwhelmingly playful, not hectoring.\"<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite news|title=Review: In \u2018The Good Dinosaur,\u2019 a Reptile Tends to His Human Pet|work=[[The New York Times]]|first=Manohla|last=Dargis|date=November 24, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/25/movies/review-the-good-dinosaur-pixar-human-and-apatosaurus.html}}</ref> Joe Morgenstern of ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' opined that \"As Pixar productions go, this one isn't a groundbreaker, but it's heartfelt and endearing, as well as visually splendiferous, and kids will love it for sure.\"<ref name=\"wsj\">{{cite news|title=\u2018The Good Dinosaur\u2019 Review: A Warm-Blooded Jurassic Lark|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|first=Joe|last=Morgenstern|date=November 25, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-good-dinosaur-review-a-warm-blooded-jurassic-lark-1448485487}}</ref> \"Clever and cloying by turns, it's a movie that always seems to be trying to evolve beyond its conventional trappings, and not succeeding as often as Pixar devotees have come to expect,\" wrote Justin Chang of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]''.<ref name=\"v\">{{cite news|title=Film Review: \u2018The Good Dinosaur\u2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Justin|last=Chang|date=November 13, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/reviews/the-good-dinosaur-review-1201639759/}}</ref> Many of the reviewers praised the sophistication of its nearly photorealistic backgrounds.<ref name=\"nyt\"/><ref name=\"ta\"/><ref name=\"bg\"/><ref name=\"twp\"/>\n\nChristopher Orr of ''[[The Atlantic]]'' felt it to be the studio's first film explicitly targeted towards children, though it is \"by no means a bad movie [...] It's a simple story, well-told.\"<ref name=\"ta\">{{cite news|title=The Good Dinosaur: Pixar\u2019s First Movie Just for Kids|work=[[The Atlantic]]|first=Christopher|last=Orr|date=November 25, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/11/the-good-dinosaur-pixars-first-movie-just-for-kids/417609/}}</ref> Mark Feeney, writing for ''[[The Boston Globe]]'', felt similarly, deeming it a \"very middling movie [...] ''The Good Dinosaur'' generally features a sort of sentimentality and emotional reductiveness that make it seem meant for small children as no previous Pixar movie has.\"<ref name=\"bg\">{{cite news|title=Pixar\u2019s \u2018The Good Dinosaur\u2019 lives in a Disney world|work=[[The Boston Globe]]|first=Mark|last=Feeney|date=November 24, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/movies/2015/11/24/pixar-latest-planet-dinosaurs/mWreOAMAHOfiTYElfIZ0UP/story.html}}</ref> ''[[The Washington Post]]''{{'s}} Stephanie Merry dubbed it \"a nice, conventional story, but it's not Pixar-level imaginative.\"<ref name=\"twp\">{{cite news|title=\u2018The Good Dinosaur\u2019 fails to live up to the Pixar promise|work=[[The Washington Post]]|first=Stephanie|last=Merry|date=November 24, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/goingoutguide/movies/the-good-dinosaur-fails-to-live-up-to-the-pixar-promise/2015/11/24/64897948-92b3-11e5-b5e4-279b4501e8a6_story.html}}</ref> [[Richard Roeper]], for the ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'', felt it \"one strange, aggressively gross and dark adventure [...] Inconsistent and weird, ''The Good Dinosaur'' is second-level Pixar all the way.\"<ref name=\"cst\">{{cite news|title='The Good Dinosaur': Not As Evolved As Most Pixar|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|author=[[Richard Roeper]]|date=November 24, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=http://entertainment.suntimes.com/movies/good-dinosaur-evolved-pixar/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226135234/http://entertainment.suntimes.com/movies/good-dinosaur-evolved-pixar/#|archive-date=December 26, 2015|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Michael Rechtshaffen of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' panned its \"disappointingly derivative\" screenplay.<ref name=\"hr\">{{cite news|title='The Good Dinosaur': Film Review|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Michael|last=Rechtshaffen|date=November 13, 2015|accessdate=December 28, 2015|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/good-dinosaur-film-review-840011}}</ref> Mark Kermode of ''[[The Guardian]]'' says \"But however much it may delight on a scene-by-scene basis, ''The Good Dinosaur'' never comes together as a coherent whole, a crucial flaw for a film by Pixar, which has always put story first.\"<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kermode|first=Mark|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/nov/29/the-good-dinosaur-pixar-animation-review|title=The Good Dinosaur review \u2013 not a Jurassic classic for Pixar|date=2015-11-29|work=The Observer|access-date=2020-03-04|last2=critic|first2=Observer film|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: LightSteelBlue;\" | List of awards and nominations\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Award\n! Date of ceremony\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n|-\n| [[American Cinema Editors Awards 2016|American Cinema Editors Awards]]\n| January 29, 2016\n| Best Edited Animated Feature Film\n| [[Stephen Schaffer]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"10\"| [[Annie Award]]s<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/in-contention/pixar-picks-up-25-annie-nominations-1201650793/ |title=\u2018Inside Out,\u2019 \u2018Good Dinosaur\u2019 Lead Annie Award Nominations|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|Penske Media Corporation]]|first=Terry|last=Flores|date=December 1, 2015|accessdate=December 4, 2015}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"10\"| [[43rd Annie Awards|February 6, 2016]]\n| [[Annie Award for Best Animated Feature|Best Animated Feature]]\n| ''The Good Dinosaur''\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement in Animated Effects in an Animated Production\n| John Reisch and Stephen Marshall\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Outstanding Achievement in Character Animation in a Feature Production\n| Mark C. Harris\n| rowspan=\"24\" {{nom}}\n|-\n| K.C. Roeyer\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement in Character Design in an Animated Feature Production\n| Matt Nolte\n|-\n| [[Annie Award for Music in a Feature Production|Outstanding Achievement in Music in an Animated Feature Production]]\n| [[Mychael Danna]] and [[Jeff Danna]]\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement in Production Design in an Animated Feature Production\n| [[Harley Jessup]], Sharon Calahan, Bryn Imagire, Noah Klocek and Huy Nguyen\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Outstanding Achievement in Storyboarding in an Animated Feature Production\n| Bill Presing\n|-\n| [[Rosana Sullivan]]\n|-\n| J.P. Vine, Tony Rosenast and Enrico Casarosa\n|-\n| [[Austin Film Critics Association Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The AFCA 2015 Awards Nominees |url=http://austinfilmcritics.org/the-afca-2015-awards-nominees/ |website=Austin Film Critics Association |accessdate=December 17, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151219011610/http://austinfilmcritics.org/the-afca-2015-awards-nominees/ |archivedate=December 19, 2015}}</ref>\n| December 29, 2015\n| Best Animated Film \n| ''The Good Dinosaur''\n|-\n| [[Black Reel Awards of 2016|Black Reel Awards]]\n| February 18, 2016\n| Best Voice Performance\n| [[Jeffrey Wright (actor)|Jeffrey Wright]] (Poppa Henry)\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[British Academy Children's Awards]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kidscreen.com/2016/10/19/horrible-histories-truetube-lead-bafta-childrens-noms/ |title=Horrible Histories, TrueTube lead BAFTA Children\u2019s noms |last=Foster |first=Elizabeth |publisher= Kidscreen|date= October 19, 2016 |accessdate= October 23, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2016/childrens/bafta-kids-vote-film |title=2016 Children's BAFTA Kids' Vote - Film |publisher= [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]]|date= November 21, 2016 |accessdate= December 2, 2016}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| November 20, 2016\n| Feature Film\n| [[Peter Sohn]] and [[Meg LeFauve]]\n|-\n| BAFTA Kids' Vote\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''The Good Dinosaur''\n|-\n| [[Chicago Film Critics Association Awards 2015|Chicago Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| December 16, 2015\n| Best Animated Film\n|-\n| [[21st Critics' Choice Awards|Critics' Choice Awards]]\n| January 17, 2016\n| Best Animated Feature\n|-\n| [[Florida Film Critics Circle Awards 2015|Florida Film Critics Circle Awards]]\n| December 23, 2015\n| Best Animated Film\n|- \n| [[Golden Globe Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/awards/golden-globe-nominations-2016-1201658153/|title='Carol,' Netflix Lead Golden Globes Nomination|last=Lang|first=Brent|date=December 10, 2015|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=December 10, 2015}}</ref>\n| [[73rd Golden Globe Awards|January 10, 2016]] \n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Animated Feature Film|Best Animated Feature Film]]\n|-\n| [[Golden Reel Award (Motion Picture Sound Editors)|Golden Reel Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|title=MOTION PICTURE SOUND EDITORS|url=https://mpse.secure-platform.com/a/gallery?roundId=6&searchParams=%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A0%2C%22sortMode%22%3A%22AscendingByApplicationName%22%2C%22displayMode%22%3A%22List%22%2C%22filterByApplicationCategoryPath%22%3A%5B59%2C67%5D%2C%22filterByWinnerCategoriesIds%22%3A%5B%5D%2C%22filterByFieldValues%22%3A%5B%5D%2C%22filterByApplicationNameOrCode%22%3A%22%22%7D|website=Motion Picture Sound Editors|accessdate=January 30, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304155742/https://mpse.secure-platform.com/a/gallery?roundId=6&searchParams=%7B%22pageIndex%22:0,%22sortMode%22:%22AscendingByApplicationName%22,%22displayMode%22:%22List%22,%22filterByApplicationCategoryP